Document: class_animationnodeblend3  
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeblend3.rst  
Summary: A resource for blending three animations in an AnimationNodeBlendTree based on a blend amount value.  

A resource to add to an AnimationNodeBlendTree. Blends two animations out of three linearly based on the amount value. This animation node has three inputs: the base animation to blend with, a "-blend" animation to blend with when the blend amount is negative, and a "+blend" animation to blend with when the blend amount is positive. The blend value should generally be in the [-1.0, 1.0] range. Values outside this range can produce amplified animations, but AnimationNodeAdd3 works better for such cases.  

Key Rule: The blend value range [-1.0, 1.0] ensures standard blending behavior, while values beyond this range are better handled by AnimationNodeAdd3.
---CHUNK---
